NOTES: Habitat: Headwaters of Rio Pomureni, west of crest of divide that separates Apurimac/Ene drainages from those fo the Poyeni and Urubamba. Most work at this camp was at close to the same elevation and below, to the N and NE of the campsite. Open pampas (sphagnum bogs) provide easy access to many kilometers in various directions. There were no flowing streams of surface water, but many water -filled large potholes and sinkholes; water logged pajonal.
